Book of Hours, Use of Paris

Library Company, 12 vol. 1. France, 15th century. This small late-fifteenth-century Book of Hours, bound in two volumes at a much later date, displays the damage characteristic of parchment books that have been exposed to fire (the parchment is wrinkled and shrunk around the edges). This is the first volume, which contains a Calendar, the Gospel Lessons, the Obsecro te, and the Hours of the Virgin of the Use of Paris.
